CAPE TOWN &#8211; South Africa&#8217;s Treasury on Tuesday said it was in talks with banks to possibly roll over around R9 billion ($695 million) worth of maturing debt due by struggling state airliner South African Airways&#8217; (SAA) at month-end, a senior official said.Treasury Director General Dondo Mogajane told legislators that should SAA fail to meet it debt obligations, it would have ripple effects on the government&#8217;s entire guarantee framework. ($1 = R12.9195 ) 